<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Request for different link in StartMenue for printers]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=501&amp;p=24268#p24268"><![CDATA[
To open Devices and Printers, specify shell:::{A8A91A66-3A7D-4424-8D24-04E180695C7A} in the Link field and nothing in the Command field.<br /><br />To open the classic Printers folder, specify shell:PrintersFolder in the Link field and nothing in the Command field.<br /><br />Are you saying that with shell:::{A8A91A66-3A7D-4424-8D24-04E180695C7A} mentioned in the Link field on your German Windows 10, it is opening the old Printers folder? In that case, that is a Windows bug. Press Win+R keys together to open the Run dialog and copy-paste shell:::{A8A91A66-3A7D-4424-8D24-04E180695C7A} into the Run dialog. See which folder exactly opens.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Wed Dec 30, 2015 9:48 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
