<author><name><![CDATA[Gaurav]]></name></author>
<updated>2013-04-10T13:14:18-07:00</updated>
<published>2013-04-10T13:14:18-07:00</published>
<id>http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=501&amp;p=2611#p2611</id>
<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=501&amp;p=2611#p2611"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Request for different link in StartMenue for printers]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=501&amp;p=2611#p2611"><![CDATA[
You can change the link yourself.<br />1. Right click the Start button, open Settings.<br />2. Enable All Settings radio button at the bottom.<br />3. Go to Customize Start menu tab.<br />4. Double click PrintersItem in the left column.<br />5. Erase the &quot;Command&quot; field: printers<br />6. In the &quot;Link&quot; field, enter:  shell:::{A8A91A66-3A7D-4424-8D24-04E180695C7A}<br />7. Check the &quot;Don't Expand&quot; checkbox at the bottom.<br />8. Click OK twice.<br /><br />Now Devices and Printers will open instead of the classic Printers folder.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Wed Apr 10, 2013 1:14 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
